---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn about Blindsided Games, the studio principles behind its incremental and strategy portfolio, and the founder building the releases."
  path="/about"
>
  <section class="section" data-reveal>
    <div class="container split-layout">
      <article class="panel panel-elevated">
        <p class="eyebrow">Studio Profile</p>
        <h1>Blindsided Games</h1>
        <p>
          Blindsided Games is an independent studio focused on systems-heavy incremental and strategy design.
          The goal is consistent: ship games with strong progression clarity, responsive UI, and long-term
          replay value across web, mobile, and desktop storefronts.
        </p>
        <div class="button-row">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Contact</a>
          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://discord.gg/dKaEy6MFCP" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Discord
          </a>
          <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://www.youtube.com/@blindsidedgames" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            YouTube
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <aside class="panel profile-card">
        <img src="/img/logo.jpg" alt="Blindsided Games logo" width="120" height="120" />
        <h2>Release Focus</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Layered progression loops that stay readable at scale</li>
          <li>Fast-loading interfaces with low-friction navigation</li>
          <li>Post-launch iteration guided by live community feedback</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" data-reveal>
    <div class="container section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Operating Principles</p>
      <h2>How the Studio Makes Decisions</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="container card-grid three-up">
      <article class="panel">
        <h3>Player Trust</h3>
        <p>Monetization and progression are built to preserve player agency and avoid manipulative loops.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="panel">
        <h3>Performance Discipline</h3>
        <p>Features are measured against runtime cost, responsiveness, and maintainability before ship.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="panel">
        <h3>Iteration Cadence</h3>
        <p>Live feedback from Discord and patch telemetry directly informs tuning and content priorities.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" data-reveal>
    <div class="container panel founder-note">
      <p class="eyebrow">Founder</p>
      <h2>Matthew Rushworth</h2>
      <p>
        I started Blindsided Games to turn systems design ideas into shipped products, not prototypes that stall.
        Since 2022, that work has grown into a multi-platform catalog, including Steam launches and active live
        updates for community-backed titles.
      </p>
      <p>
        My focus is practical execution: clear information architecture, durable progression design, and fast
        iteration cycles that keep each release improving after launch.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside development, I am a father building games around real-world time constraints. That perspective
        shapes every product decision: the game should be rewarding, understandable, and respectful of player time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
